Recommendations:


 36.1 Enhance the CRR model to include:
 o the jurisdictions in which a Seller operates in;
 o the jurisdiction in which a UBO is a resident in, if different to the jurisdiction the Seller is incorporated in;
 o the age of the Seller;
 o whether the structure is opaque or presents any high-risk factors (i.e., bearer shares or nominee shareholder);
 o estimated average transaction value 
 o estimated volume of transactions;
 o annual turnover; and 
 o how the Seller will receive payment. 


 36.2 Increase the risk of Sole Proprietors to high and decrease the risk of Limited Companies to moderate.


 36.3 Ensure the variables and factors that are part of the aCRR model are fully documented.


 36.4 Ensure the risk factors considered within the CRR model, and the Skilled Person’s suggestion above form part of the aCRR mode to ensure the model is capable of capturing industry risk, expected behaviour, and actual behaviour. "


 36.5 Increases the MCC risk rating for the following: o markets; o Restaurants; o health and beauty spas; o tanning salon; and o hair removal.


